==English==
===Etymology===
The term refers to the ball crushing the foot of the batsman, if not played with their bat.  [[sandshoe|Sandshoe]] is not literal though, batsmen wear sturdy boots, not sandshoes, when batting.
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# {{cricket}} A [[yorker]] bowled at the batsman's feet.
